emacs

Global Bindings Starting With M-s:
key             binding
---             -------

M-s h           Prefix Command
M-s o           occur
M-s w           isearch-forward-word

M-s h f         hi-lock-find-patterns
M-s h l         highlight-lines-matching-regexp
M-s h p         highlight-phrase
M-s h r         highlight-regexp
M-s h u         unhighlight-regexp
M-s h w         hi-lock-write-interactive-patterns

C-M-s   Begin incremental regexp search (isearch-forward-regexp).

C-M-r  Begin reverse incremental regexp search (isearch-backward-regexp).


C-x o - switch windows

C-x C-b buffer list

M-x undo-all / Repeat the undo command (C-/ or C-x u or C-_ ) 

C-x x g  revert-buffer

C-x z: This will repeat the last command exactly.


To set the large-file-warning-threshold variable, you can use the following steps:

Press C-h v large-file-warning-threshold to get help on this variable.

Press M-x customize-variable RET large-file-warning-threshold to open the customization buffer for this variable.

Enter a new value for the variable and press Enter.

Press C-x C-s to save your changes.

C-x space to select block 

Search History - C-s C-s you search the previous word. Then M-p (and M-n) for history.

use M-s h . to highlight the current word, and it will use your custom face.

To make the cursor even more visible, you can use HL Line mode, a minor mode that highlights the line containing point. 

Use M-x hl-line-mode to enable or disable it in the current buffer. 

M-x global-hl-line-mode enables or disables the same mode globally.

use M-e at any time during Isearch to edit the search string.
